# IMPORTANT: Image Management Strategy
# ====================================
# By DEFAULT, this .gitignore ALLOWS image files to be tracked in git
# This keeps your generated images backed up in version control
#
# Images stored locally in:
# - images/features/*.webp        (6 feature images)
# - images/how-it-works/*.webp    (5 step images)
# - images/misc/*.webp            (other images as needed)
#
# Why track images in git?
# ✓ Keeps all project assets in one place
# ✓ Easy collaboration with version history
# ✓ Images backup with code changes
# ✓ No external dependencies or CDN needed
#
# If you have VERY LARGE image files and want to exclude them:
# Uncomment ONLY the lines you need below
#
# images/features/*.webp
# images/features/*.png
# images/features/*.jpg
# images/how-it-works/*.webp
# images/how-it-works/*.png
# images/how-it-works/*.jpg
# images/misc/*.webp
# images/misc/*.png
# images/misc/*.jpg

# Exclude only temporary image files
images/**/*.tmp
images/**/*.bak
images/**/*.swp

# Keep documentation and guides
!images/
!images/features/
!images/how-it-works/
!images/misc/
!images/IMAGE_GUIDE.md